a Tech  Colonel Scarpaci has completed the marketing track of the Post Doctoral Bridge Program to Business taught by the Pampline College of Business at Virginia Tech  Colonel Scarpaci has already published extensively in health care  tourism  and international development  In addition to Principles of Marketing and Business Marketing  he will be teaching a course on International Marketing  This course  wherein cadets will travel to Chile over the winter break  will introduce cadets to marketing strategies found abroad    Spring 2009 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Major Field Test in Business  Colonel Husted Retires  New Hire   Colonel Scarpaci  Faculty Scholarship  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  SBD and ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 